1 (a) Each county sheriff, in consultation with the
2 board of county commissioners, shall negotiate the terms of
3 and enter into a written agreement between the county and
4 the United States attorney general or department of
5 justice, as provided by 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g), for the
6 enforcement of federal immigration and customs laws,
7 detentions, removals and investigations in Wyoming. The
8 agreement shall be signed by the sheriff and the board of
9 county commissioners or as otherwise required by the
10 appropriate federal agency.
11
12 (b) Not later than October 1, 2025 and each October 1
13 thereafter, each county sheriff shall report to the Wyoming
14 attorney general on:
15
16 (i) The status of negotiations with the United
17 States attorney general and the status of any agreement
18 entered into under 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g);
19
20 (ii) Whether the United States attorney general
21 has declined to enter into an agreement with the county
22 under 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) and the reasons for declining;
23
