1 (iii) If the United States attorney general has
2 declined to enter into an agreement with the county, the
3 county's communication and cooperation with the United
4 States attorney general under 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g).
5
6 (c) Not later than November 1, 2025 and each November
7 1 thereafter, the attorney general shall report to the
8 joint judiciary interim committee on the information that
9 each county sheriff communicated to the Wyoming attorney
10 general under subsection (b) of this section.
11
12 (d) A county that fails to enter or fails to attempt
13 to enter into an agreement required by subsection (a) of
14 this section shall not be eligible to receive any state
15 administered federal funds associated with law enforcement
16 and law enforcement training for each fiscal year in which
17 the county is not in compliance with subsection (a) of this
18 section. A county that has reported to the Wyoming attorney
19 general that the United States attorney general has
20 declined to enter into an agreement under 8 U.S.C. §
21 1357(g) shall not be subject to this subsection.
